FBIS3-10167 "drlat041_c_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Mar 1994 MEXICO Subcommander Marcos Requests U.S. Aid PA0103152694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 1 Mar 94 PA0103152694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 1300 GMT 1 Mar 94 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "At the First Hour" newscast] [Text] Subcommander Marcos held a news conference for the U.S. media on 28 March; during this news conference, he requested U.S. aid: [Begin Subcommander Marcos recording, in English] We want the U.S. people to help us with medicines, clothes, milk, but the first and most important thing we want is for them to know the right reason for our struggle. We think the Clinton administration is upset about us. They do not know if there is really no foreign nation behind us. I think the computer of the CIA and the FBI and the State Department they do not have any response [sentence as heard]. They put in the computer: Subcommander Marcos, he has a big nose. They put these facts in the computer, and there is no answer, because there is no more Soviet Union, the Cubans are cornered. The people's struggle in Central America, they are behind history and the computer there is mad. [sentence as heard] It is crazy about us. Maybe they are looking for Subcommander Marcos' past. Was he in the Soviet Union, Havana, Managua, Mexico, Tepito? [end recording]
